<title>USA: Santa Cruz sets restructuring.</title>
<headline>Santa Cruz sets restructuring.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CRUZ, Calif. 1997-06-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Santa Cruz Operation Inc,, a leading supplier of UNIX server operating systems, said on Wednesday it will restructure its organization to integrate its multiple product development groups into a single product engineering and marketing division to be headed by UNIX pioneer Doug Michels, the company's co-founder, executive vice president, and chief technical officer.</p>
<p>Additionally, Santa Cruz said, it is accelerating its move to electronic distribution of software explaining that this new model requires far less inventory in the distribution channel than has historically been necessary.</p>
